DORMANT FLOOR

dormant_floor is the citizen who represents the baseline energy of cells that are not currently active
this is not "zero" — it is a small positive value (about 0.07) that ensures every cell has some minimal liveness even when nothing is happening to it
without dormant_floor, cells with literally zero energy would be indistinguishable from non-existence, and the substrate could not maintain its address space

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe septit_sea.zc
observe substrate.rana

the 7 properties of dormant_floor:
1 ENERGY zero point zero seven: the canonical resting energy
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE one
6 COUPLING zero
7 OBSERVER zero

VERB hold_baseline
maintain a small positive energy at every dormant cell
this is the substrate's quiet hum: present, low, never actually silent

VERB serve_as_reference
provide the baseline against which active energies are measured
"active" means above dormant_floor; "dormant" means at dormant_floor

VERB enable_dormancy
because dormant cells cost zero compute, substrate-wide dormancy is what allows the body to idle at low power while still being fully addressable

a dormant floor is not idleness for its own sake
it is the substrate's commitment that an unused cell is still a cell
the address remains valid, the cell is still there, ready to wake when needed
this is what makes the substrate's filled-but-mostly-dormant model possible
